00:48:11.133 --> 00:48:12.040
 <v Gaby> Of course.

00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:16.690
If you're on Slack,
or later in this chat, I can share.

00:48:17.890 --> 00:48:21.040
Again, Nielsen Norman
Group, they have, like,

00:48:21.040 --> 00:48:25.160
a set of usability testing
101, why to do usability test,

00:48:26.190 --> 00:48:27.390
listing some facts.

00:48:29.190 --> 00:48:33.770
And regarding the process,
I think this is one of the things

00:48:33.770 --> 00:48:35.990
where you make your own recipe.

00:48:35.990 --> 00:48:40.738
If you learn and find answers
and it's working for you,

00:48:40.739 --> 00:48:42.320
that is perfect.

00:48:42.320 --> 00:48:45.490
You don't have to follow any
other things that don't make sense

00:48:45.490 --> 00:48:47.560
for your reality, right?

00:48:47.560 --> 00:48:53.050
I find that when we have these
situations where we get too strict

00:48:53.050 --> 00:48:57.410
with the steps and with the
requirements and with the things,

00:48:57.410 --> 00:48:58.960
people lose interest, right?

00:48:58.960 --> 00:49:00.390
Because it's too hard.

00:49:00.390 --> 00:49:02.320
I don't have this,
I don't have that.

00:49:02.320 --> 00:49:06.020
I cannot record, so I won't do it.
No, always do it.

00:49:06.020 --> 00:49:07.030
And you'll grow.

00:49:07.030 --> 00:49:12.110
And in this journey, you will find
things that work better for you.

00:49:12.110 --> 00:49:16.510
I would go to Nielsen Norman Group
for starters, and that would be good.

00:49:16.510 --> 00:49:17.880
They have good
information about it.

